<HEADLINE> Squillari Through to Semi-finals at Stuttgart Open </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BERLIN, July 21 (Xinhua) -- Franco Squillari of Argentina
cruised into the semi-finals of the Stuttgart Open men's tennis
tournament by defeating Slovakia's Karol Kucera in straight sets
on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Fifth seed Squillari, the only seed alive in the tournament,
downed his opponent 7-5, 6-1 to set up a clash with German Wild
Card Daniel Elsner for a berth in the final.
</P>
<P>
Elsner, who knocked out defending champion and top seed Magnus
Norman of Sweden on Thursday, took just 53 minutes to overwhelm
Czech Jiri Novak 6-2, 6-1.
</P>
<P>
Andrew Ilie of Australia also made it through to the semifinals
with a 6-3, 6-4 victory over German Rainer Schuettler. Ilie now
faces either Ukraine's Andrei Medvedev or Argentine Gaston Gaudio.
</P>
<P>
Medvedev ousted second seed Russian Yevgeny Kafelnikov 6-7, 7-5,
6-3 in a postponed second round match early on Friday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
