<HEADLINE> Xinhua Mideast News Summary at 2000GMT, Saturday </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BAGHDAD -- Iraq is determined to raise its oil output by self-
reliance instead of oil contracts, the official Iraqi News Agency
(INA) reported on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Citing an official of the Iraqi oil ministry, the INA said that
even if Iraq does not conclude contracts with foreign companies to
develop oil fields, Iraq is still to raise its crude oil output.
</P>
<P>
Iraqi Oil Minister Amir Muhammad Rashid stated recently that
Iraq will upgrade its crude oil output to 3.5 million barrels per
day (bpd) by the end of this year. (BC-Iraq-Oil)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
GAZA -- No progress has been achieved on any of the crucial
issues being discussed at Camp David, said Secretary General of the
Executive Committee of Palestine Liberation Organization (PLO)
Mahmoud Abbas Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The gaps between the Palestinians and Israel are "still wide"
not only on the issue of Jerusalem, but also on the Palestinian
refugees, borders of a future Palestinian state and security, said
Abbas, who is also known as Abu Mazen.  (Palestine-Talks)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
CAIRO -- Egypt and Jordan stressed on Saturday East Jerusalem is
part of the Arab territories occupied by Israel in 1967 and subject
to the relevant United Nations resolutions that demand Israel to
return those lands.
</P>
<P>
Arab countries see East Jerusalem as subject to the U.N.
Resolution 242 because it was occupied by Israel in 1967, Jordanian
Foreign Minister Abdel Ilah al-Khatib said after meeting with his
Egyptian counterpart Amr Moussa in Alexandria. (Egypt-Jordan-
Jerusalem)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
CAIRO -- India on Saturday denied reports about its pledge to
carry out nuclear cooperation with Israel, which has prompted
condemnation throughout the Arab world.
</P>
<P>
The Indian embassy in Cairo said in a statement that it was
disturbed by the claims published in some newspapers, which it said
could badly affect India's relationship with Arab countries.
</P>
<P>
India asks Arabs to know that its relationship with Israel will
not be at the expense of its traditional relations with the Arab
countries, the embassy said. (Egypt-India-Israel) 
</P>
</TEXT>
