<HEADLINE> Britain Announces New Sanctions Against Fiji </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, July 22 (Xinhua) -- Britain has announced new sanctions
against Fiji following its unrest which ended a hostage crisis but
denied its ethnic Indian minority any significant role in
government.
</P>
<P>
The BBC quoted John Battle, Foreign Minister, Saturday as
saying that "financial assistance would be cancelled, along with
planned Royal Navy visits and joint military exercises".
</P>
<P>
Stressing the importance of an early return to full "democracy",
Battle said Britain would not issue licenses for any arms or
security equipment for export to Fiji.
</P>
<P>
