with a deal which saw rebel leader George Speight and several of
his supporters included in a new cabinet but no cabinet role for
anyone from the Indian population.
</P>
<P>
In a statement, Battle said: "We are determined to pursue a
commitment by the Fijian authorities to a timetable for return to
democratic government based on a fair constitution."
</P>
<P>
"We are pressing our EU partners to impose restrictions on
travel by George Speight and his associates. We are cancelling all
foreign office funded assistance to Fiji's government," he added.
</P>
