<HEADLINE> Gustafsson Reaches Dutch Open Final </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, July 22 (Xinhua) -- Sweden's Magnus Gustafsson beat
Dutch youngster Edwin Kempes 6-4, 6-4 to reach the final of the
Dutch Open men's tennis tournament in Amsterdam on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Fourth seed Gustafsson, who is vying for his 14th tournament
title, needed one break to take the opening set.
</P>
<P>
In the second set, the 33-year-old Sweden, who was a former
world top-10 player, broke Kempes in the opening game but lost his
service at 3-2 with a double fault on the last point.
</P>
<P>
Gustafsson, who won the event in 1991, broke back immediately
on his way to victory.
</P>
<P>
Raemon Sluiter of the Netherlands also booked a berth in the
final after downing Russian teenager and qualifier Nikola
Davydenko 6-2, 7-6 (7-5). It will be the first ATP final for the
22-year-old Dutchman. 
