<HEADLINE> Europeans Dominate in Women's, Mixed Doubles at Indonesia Open Badminton </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, July 22 (Xinhua) -- Indonesia maintained its supremacy
in the men's doubles while Europeans are ensured champions in
women's doubles and mixed doubles in the Sanyo Indonesian Open
here on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
In all-Indonesian semifinals in the men's doubles, top seeded
Candra Wijaya/Tony Gunawan beat Sigit Budiarto/Halim Heryanto 15-7,
15-11, but 1996 Olympics champion Ricky Subagjo/Rexy Mainaky lost
to Flandy Limpele/Eng Hian 6-15, 9-15.
</P>
<P>
Indonesian will grab another title in the men's singles if
Taufik Hidayat can beat Ong Ewe Hock from Malaysia in the final on
Sunday.
</P>
<P>
In the men's singles semifinals, the third seed Taufik beat
giant killer Roslin Hashim from Malaysia 15-11, 15-5 and Ong Ewe
Hock defeated Johan Hadikusuma of Indonesia 15-9, 15-4.
</P>
<P>
Both Taufik and Ong believed that their chance to clinch the
title is 50-50. Taufik said his self-confidence had increased
after reaching the semifinals. Ong stressed that he once beat
Taufik in international meetings.
</P>
<P>
However, no Indonesian players will take part in the finals in
three other divisions.
</P>
<P>
In women's singles semifinals, defending champion Lidya
Djaelawidja lost to top seed Camilla Martin of Denmark 7-11, 2-11.
Martin will meet Wang Chen from Hong Kong, who defeated Kelly
Morgan of Wales 11-0, 11-4, in the final.
</P>
<P>
In women's doubles semifinals, second seed Joanne Goode/Donna
Kellogg of Britain and third seed Nicole van Hooren/Lotte
Jonathans of the Netherlands beat their Indonesian opponents
respectively to set up a clash in Sunday's final.
</P>
<P>
Indonesian Tri Kusharyanto/Minarti Timur who were seeking a
record sixth successive mixed doubles title was dashed when they
lost to fifth seed Simon Archer/Joanne Goode of Britain on
Saturday, the scores are 15-7, 13-15, 10-15.
</P>
<P>
Top seed Michael Sogaard/Rikke Olsen of Denmark eliminated
another Indonesian pair Bambang Supriyanto/Zelin Resiana with 15-7,
15-3. Simon Archer/Joanne Goode and Michael Sogaard/Rikke Olsen
will vie for the title on Sunday. 
</P>
