<HEADLINE> China Fights Against RMB Counterfeiting </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 22 (Xinhua) -- China has so far uncovered 5,346
RMB counterfeiting cases involving 6,537 suspects, and confiscated
a total of 280 million yuan (about 33.6 million U.S. dollars) in
fake Chinese currency, the Renminbi (RMB).
</P>
<P>
During a meeting held here today on the battle against
counterfeit currency, government officials emphasized the crucial
role of the drive in maintaining social stability and order in
economic and financial transactions.
</P>
<P>
China started a drive against RMB counterfeiting in 16
provinces in April this year.
</P>
<P>
Dai Xianglong, president of the People's Bank of China, at the
meeting ordered all the related departments to continue their
efforts and further cooperate in the drive, while gaining more
support from the general public.  
</P>
