<HEADLINE> Qinghua Scholars Back From Tibet Tour </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LHASA, July 22 (Xinhua) -- A ten-member team from Qinghua
University left for Beijing today after a 12-day visit to
southwest China's Tibet Autonomous Region.
</P>
<P>
Fan Huizheng, head of the team, said the team members, all
holding doctorates, gave 13 lectures on such subjects as
economics, information, biology, construction and environmental
protection, all important branches of knowledge for the Western
China development project.
</P>
<P>
Fan said they also introduced 231 technological items to the
region, and signed 13 letters of intent with Tibet on Internet
development, regional economic research, solar energy use and high-
quality cattle breeding.
</P>
<P>
Wang Ning, a team member, said he used to have scant knowledge
of the remote area, but the visit had made him aware of Tibet's
crucial strategic role in the national economy and modernization
drive, and also in national defense and the efforts to combat
splittism, which requires nationwide support.
</P>
<P>
The visit was a good opportunity to get to know more about the
rapid development in Tibet in recent years, which left a deep
impression on them, said the team members.  
</P>
