<HEADLINE> International Arts Carnival Opens in HK </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, July 22 (Xinhua) -- The International Arts Carnival
opened Saturday at the Hong Kong Cultural Center.
</P>
<P>
The opening ceremony was officiated by Professor Chang Hsin-
kang, chairman of the Culture and Heritage Commission and Paul
Leung, director of Leisure and Cultural Services.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the opening ceremony, Leung said, "The
International Arts Carnival aims to inspire and promote interests
in arts among our children and youngsters. With the staunch and
support from parents, we hope our young generation will become
more knowledgeable and spiritually enriched."
</P>
<P>
The six-week International Arts Carnival features about 1,000
local and international artists from 50 performing groups in
nearly 80 entertaining and educational shows as well as 80
workshops.
</P>
<P>
There are three main program highlights, namely "Midsummer
Night Series," "Treasure Series" and "Chinese Culture Series."
</P>
<P>
Other programs in the event include activities organized by
museums and libraries, Poster Design Competition and Exhibition
and guided tours. 
</P>
