<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Shaanxi Earmarks 2.2 Billion Yuan for Telecom Upgrading </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XI'AN, July 22 (Xinhua) -- Shaanxi Province in northwest China
is to inject another 2.2 billion yuan this year into upgrading its
telecommunications network, a leading telecom operator said here
today.
</P>
<P>
Zhou Shifu, president of Shanxi Telecom, said at the
inauguration ceremony of this branch of China Telecom here today
that his company will focus its development efforts on increasing
fixed-line usage and building an information expressway based on
its fiber-optical and broadband telecommunications networks.
</P>
<P>
Fixed-line phone users in Shaanxi so far exceed three million,
which means that one in ten persons in the province owns a fixed-
line phone, according to Zhou.
</P>
<P>
The telecommunications industry has been considered the fastest-
growing economic sector in Shaanxi for the past 20 years. Fiber-
optical telecommunication has become a reality in all counties and
most of the townships in the province. Meanwhile, the number of
phone users increased by 400,000 in 1999, and by 580,000 in the
first six months of this year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
