<HEADLINE> Preparations for ICOLD Conference Going Smoothly </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 22 (Xinhua) -- The preparations for the 68th
annual meeting of the International Commission on Large Dams (
ICOLD) and the 20th International Dam Conference are going
smoothly, according to its sponsors.
</P>
<P>
Wang Shucheng, minister of water resources, told a press
conference here today that China's Three Gorges Project, involving
the largest dam in the world, will be a subject at the meeting.
</P>
<P>
He said that 2,000 participants from both developed and
developing countries will attend the gathering, which is scheduled
to open in September this year.
</P>
<P>
The meeting will also discuss issues of flooding, safety and
economic efficiency concerning dams, he said.
</P>
<P>
The ICOLD, with 81 member countries, was established in 1928 to
exchange information and strengthen technical cooperation.
</P>
<P>
With abundant water resources and frequent floods, China is a
country that is continually involved in dam construction. 
</P>
</TEXT>
