<DATE_TIME> 2000-07-22 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's Defense Industry Shows Signs of Recovery </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 22 (Xinhua) -- China's defense industry is still
running in the red, but its efficiency has improved, government
officials announced here today.
</P>
<P>
According to the announcement, the China Weaponry Equipment
Group, which has 57 subsidiary companies, saw its output value
reach 10.7 billion yuan (about 1.2 billion U.S. dollars) in the
first half of this year, an increase of 4.36 percent over the same
period of 1999.
</P>
<P>
Another conglomerate, the China Weaponry Industry Group, which
has 83 subsidiary companies, generated 6.67 billion yuan in output
value in the same period.
</P>
<P>
The two groups have reduced their economic losses by 23.9
percent and 11.9 percent, respectively, compared with last year,
according to government figures.
</P>
<P>
Both of them have changed their focus to producing civilian
products, including cars and motorcycles, instead of solely
armaments, since the beginning of the 1990s. 
</P>
</TEXT>
