<HEADLINE> China Opens Its Longest Domestic Air Line </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARBIN, July 22 (Xinhua) -- China has opened its longest
domestic air line, which stretches north-south from Jiamusi City
in northeast China's Heilongjiang Province, to Sanya City in the
country's southernmost province of Hainan.
</P>
<P>
There will be two flights a week to cover a distance of 4,243
km. Jiamusi is a major commercial grain base and industrial center
in northeast China and Sanya is well known as a coastal resort.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, another new air route between Jiamusi and Shenzhen
in south China's Guangdong Province, went into operation, with
four flights a week. 
</P>
</TEXT>
