<HEADLINE> Beijing Int'l Horn Festival Starts </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 22 (Xinhua) -- The 32nd International Horn
Society (IHS) Symposium and 2000 Beijing International Horn
Festival started this evening at Beijing's Century Theater.
</P>
<P>
More than 250 overseas horn soloists and 500 Chinese musicians
are participating in the one-week musical event, sponsored by the
Chinese Musicians Association (CMA) and the China International
Youth Exchange Center.
</P>
<P>
At the inaugural symphony concert this evening, some well-known
horn musicians, accompanied by the China Opera Theater Symphony
Orchestra, provided a splendid performance.
</P>
<P>
Organizers with the Century Performance Company said that the
symposium and festival will include lectures given by world horn
masters, academic workshops, a horn exhibition, a contest and 17
concerts.
</P>
<P>
Chinese music fans will also have opportunities to enjoy solo
performances from world-famous horn players Froydis Ree Wekre,
Peter Kurau and Hans Pizka, and promising Chinese musicians Zhang
Chengxin, Tang Bing and Jia Hui.
</P>
<P>
The performance schedule of 17 concerts includes most of the
classical horn pieces composed by Mozart, Beethoven, Wagner and
other masters, the organizers said.
</P>
<P>
Established in 1969, the IHS links people who have a common
interest in the horn. The society, with over 3,000 members,
organizes a symposium every year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
