<DATE_TIME> 2000-07-22 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ancient City Blocks to Be Protected </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The old streets and residence communities maintain the unique
features of Beijing, capital of several ancient dynasties, the
People's Daily has reported.
</P>
<P>
The latest move initiated by the local government shows Beijing
's determination to preserve its treasured heritage, including
ancient buildings, the newspaper said.
</P>
<P>
Under strict preservation are Xihuamen Street, Donghuamen
Street, Wenjin Street, Dongjiaomin Alley, and others, according to
the Beijing City Landscaping Committee,
</P>
<P>
The municipal government started to pay attention to protection
of ancient streets and blocks in 1990. Since then, relics experts
in the city have repeatedly appealed for the drafting of a
specific protection plan as soon as possible, in a drive to
attract more overseas tourists.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the local authorities are formulating relevant laws
and regulations to help harmonize the urbanization process with
cultural relics protection. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
