<DOCNO> XIE20000722.0069 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-07-22 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Sudan, Ethiopia to Cancel Visa </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KHARTOUM, July 22 (Xinhua) -- Ethiopia's charge d'affairs in
Sudan
Abdou Bishri said the two countries have agreed to issue unified
cards
to facilitate the crossing of cars and the safe movement and
passage
of Sudanese and Ethiopian nationals.
</P>
<P>
Local daily Alanbaa on Saturday quoted the Ethiopian diplomat as
saying that individuals from both countries will no longer need
visas to enter the other country when the accord takes effect.
</P>
<P>
He said that the Ethiopian government had printed the cards and
presented them to the Sudanese Ministry of Communications.
</P>
<P>
Relations between neighboring Sudan and Ethiopia deteriorated in
1995 and the level of Ethiopian diplomatic representation in Sudan
was reduced following a failed assasination attempt against
visiting Egyptian President Hosni Mubarak in Ethiopian capital of
Addis Ababa.
</P>
<P>
Ethiopia accused Sudan was behind the attempted assasination
carried out by Egyptian Islamic militants. Ties between the two
countries have been improved since March when the Sudanese-
Ethiopian joint ministerial committee convened.
</P>
<P>
And the Ethiopian government has expressed support to the
measures taken by Sudan to achieve economic development and
national reconciliation in the country, where years of civil war
and ensuing famine have claimed nearly 2 million lives. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
