<HEADLINE> China Through to Team Finals at Asian Junior Badminton Championships </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, July 22 (Xinhua) -- China secured both berths in the
boys' and girls' team finals in the Asian junior badminton
championships in Kyoto on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The second-seeded Chinese boys outplayed Malaysia 3-1 in the
best-of-five semi-finals after a 3-0 victory over India in the
quarter-finals and set up a re-match against Indonesia in the
final.
</P>
<P>
Top-seeded defending champions Indonesia, who beat China 3-1 in
last year's final, crushed Chinese Taipei and South Korea both 3-0
on their way to the final.
</P>
<P>
In the girls' semi-finals, defending champion China eased past
Chinese Taipei 3-0 and second-seeded South Korea were 3-1 winners
over host Japan. 
</P>
