<HEADLINE> Three Universities in Shandong Province Merge </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JINAN, July 22 (Xinhua) -- Three universities in east China's
Shandong Province merged and formed the New Shandong University
today.
</P>
<P>
The new university was set up by merging Shandong University,
Shandong Medical Sciences University and Shandong Engineering
University.
</P>
<P>
The university now has more than 35,000 faculty members and
students, including 718 professors.
</P>
<P>
Zhan Tao, 37, has been appointed president of the New Shandong
University.
</P>
<P>
This merger, part of the nationwide reform of the educational
system, is expected to enhance the functions of Chinese
universities by making the most of the advantages of different
higher-educational institutions, according to officials at the
Ministry of Education.
</P>
<P>
In recent years, China has merged a number of universities to
make them more competitive. 
</P>
