<HEADLINE> China, Thailand to Strengthen Tourism Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, July 22 (Xinhua) -- China and Thailand reached an
agreement here today on strengthening cooperation in the tourism
industry.
</P>
<P>
Pradech Phayakvichien, director of the Tourism Administration
of Thailand, told a seminar here today that 800,000 Chinese
visited Thailand in 1999, and China has become Thailand's third-
largest tourist source.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, many Thai people have visited China, and Thailand
has become a channel for Western tourists to enter China, he said.
</P>
<P>
He estimated that more than one million Chinese will travel to
his country in 2001.
</P>
<P>
He said that Thailand will improve its tourism environment, and
open more routes to attract Chinese visitors.
</P>
<P>
The seminar, sponsored by the Thai consulate in Shanghai, was
held to mark the 25th anniversary of the establishment of
diplomatic relations between the two countries. 
</P>
