<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China to Build More Highways in West </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHENGDU, July 22 (Xinhua) -- China will build more highways in
its western region, including two linking the heartland with the
Tibet Autonomous Region, over the next five to 10 years.
</P>
<P>
One of the roads will link Dandong city in northeast China's
Liaoning province with Lhasa, capital of Tibet, and the other will
link this capital of Sichuan Province with Zhangmu,also in Tibet,
Vice-Premier Wu Bangguo told a meeting on transportation
development here today.
</P>
<P>
There are already three highways linking the inland areas with
Tibet.
</P>
<P>
Wu said that China will also build another 14 main highways in
the western region in the coming ten years.
</P>
<P>
He added that China will have completed a modern highway
network in the west by 2030.
</P>
<P>
At the moment, roads in the western region are poor and
insufficient. There are only 7.8 km of highways per 100 sq km in
the region, only half of the national average.
</P>
<P>
China has made the improvement of infrastructure the priority
in its program to develop the vast western region.  
</P>
</TEXT>
