<HEADLINE> Foreign Trade of Major Chinese Regions: Chongqing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 22 (Xinhua) -- Xinhua is releasing major economic
indicators of ten major Chinese regions in the first half of this
year.
</P>
<P>
The ten regions are: Guangdong, Jiangsu, Shandong, Zhejiang,
Henan, Liaoning, Shanghai, Beijing, Tianjin, and Chongqing. These
provinces and municipalities make up the bulk of the Chinese
economy.
</P>
<P>
The following is the foreign trade performance in Chongqing,
one of China's four municipalities, in the first six months of
this year:
</P>
<P>
Foreign trade in Chongqing reached 783 million US dollars, up
72.8 percent over the year-ago period.
</P>
<P>
The total included 386 million US dollars in exports, up 103
percent, and 397 million US dollars in imports, up 51 percent.
</P>
</TEXT>
