<HEADLINE> Market Index of Major Chinese Regions: Chongqing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 22 (Xinhua) -- Xinhua is releasing major economic
indicators of ten major Chinese regions in the first half of this
year.
</P>
<P>
The ten regions are: Guangdong, Jiangsu, Shandong, Zhejiang,
Henan, Liaoning, Shanghai, Beijing, Tianjin, and Chongqing. These
provinces and municipalities make up the bulk of the Chinese
economy.
</P>
<P>
The following is the consumer market situation in Chongqing,
one of China's four municipalities, in the first six months of
this year:
</P>
<P>
The city's retail sales of consumer goods totaled 31.87 billion
yuan in the January-June period, a rise of 13.6 percent from the
year-ago period.
</P>
<P>
Of the total, 18.24 billion yuan were from local urban areas,
up 9 percent, and 13.63 billion yuan from rural areas, up 6.8
percent. 
</P>
