<HEADLINE> Agricultural Index of Major Chinese Regions: Chongqing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 22 (Xinhua) -- Xinhua is releasing dispatches on
major economic indicators of ten major Chinese regions in the
first half of this year.
</P>
<P>
The ten regions include Guangdong, Jiangsu, Shandong, Zhejiang,
Henan Liaoning, Shanghai, Beijing, Tianjin, and Chongqing. These
provinces and municipalities make up the bulk of the Chinese
economy.
</P>
<P>
The following is the agricultural situation in Chongqing, one
of China's four municipalities, in the first half of the year:
</P>
<P>
Chongqing achieved 47.49 billion yuan in agricultural output
value in the January-June period, up 21.8 percent from the same
period last year, and its agricultural added value hit 10.8
billion yuan, an increase of 19.6 percent.
</P>
<P>
The acreage sown to summer crops were 124.3 million mu (8.29
million ha) in the first six months, 6.9 percent less than the
same period last year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
