<HEADLINE> Fixed Assets Investment Index of Major Chinese Regions: Chongqing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 22 (Xinhua) -- Xinhua is releasing dispatches on
major economic indicators of ten major Chinese regions in the
first quarter of this year.
</P>
<P>
The ten regions include Guangdong, Jiangsu, Shandong, Zhejiang,
Henan, Liaoning, Shanghai, Beijing, Tianjin, and Chongqing. These
provinces and municipalities make up the bulk of the Chinese
economy.
</P>
<P>
The following is the latest development in fixed assets
investment in Chongqing, one of China's four municipalities, in
the first six months of the year:
</P>
<P>
Chongqing injected 16 billion yuan in fixed assets from January
to June, an increase of 35.4 percent over the same period last
year. The volume included two major parts: 8.67 billion yuan in
the infrastructure construction sector, up 36.4 percent, and 4.65
billion yuan in real estate sector, up 27.5 percent.  
