<HEADLINE> Financial Index of Major Chinese Regions: Chongqing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 22 (Xinhua) -- Xinhua is releasing dispatches on
major economic indicators of ten major Chinese regions in the
first half of this year.
</P>
<P>
The ten regions include Guangdong, Jiangsu, Shandong, Zhejiang,
Henan, Liaoning, Shanghai, Beijing, Tianjin, and Chongqing. These
provinces and municipalities make up the bulk of the Chinese
economy.
</P>
<P>
The following is the financial situation in Chongqing, one of
China's four municipalities, in the first quarter of the year:
</P>
<P>
The outstanding amount of all deposits in Chongqing hit 172
billion yuan by June, 14 billion yuan more than the beginning of
the year. Of the total volume, 100.9 billion yuan were local
residents' savings deposits, up by 10 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
The city's total loans reached 172.3 billion yuan, 11.1 billion
yuan more than the beginning of the year.  
</P>
</TEXT>
