<HEADLINE> Economic Index of Major Chinese Regions: Chongqing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 22 (Xinhua) -- Xinhua is releasing dispatches on
major economic indicators of ten major Chinese regions in the
first half of this year.
</P>
<P>
The ten regions include Guangdong, Jiangsu, Shandong, Zhejiang,
Henan Liaoning, Shanghai, Beijing, Tianjin, and Chongqing. These
provinces and municipalities make up the bulk of the Chinese
economy.
</P>
<P>
The following is a general economic development in Chongqing,
one of China's four municipalities, in the first six months of the
year:
</P>
<P>
Chongqing's gross domestic product (GDP) amounted to 70.4
billion yuan in the January-June period, reporting a growth of 8.3
percent over the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
The city achieved 10.2 billion yuan in the added value of
agriculture, up one percent. It also registered 10.1 percent and 8.
4 percent increases in its second and third industries with added
value reaching 30.5 billion yuan and 29.7 billion yuan,
respectively.  
</P>
