<HEADLINE> Income Index of Major Chinese Regions: Chongqing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 22 (Xinhua) -- Xinhua is releasing dispatches on
major economic indicators of ten major Chinese regions in the
first half of this year.
</P>
<P>
The ten regions include Guangdong, Jiangsu, Shandong, Zhejiang,
Henan Liaoning, Shanghai, Beijing, Tianjin, and Chongqing. These
provinces and municipalities make up the bulk of the Chinese
economy.
</P>
<P>
The following is the latest income situation for urban and
rural dwellers in Chongqing, one of China's four municipalities,
in the first six months of the year:
</P>
<P>
The average per capita disposable income of urban residents in
Chongqing reached 3,230 yuan in the period, an increase of 12.7
percent over the year-ago period.
</P>
<P>
The per capita net income of rural dwellers topped 771 yuan, up
10 percent.  
