<HEADLINE> Jacobs Runs Best Women's 5,000m of Year in U.S. Olympic Trials </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, July 21 (Xinhua) -- Regina Jacobs clocked the best
time of the year in the women's 5,000 meters final and improved
her own American record in the U.S. athletics Olympic trials on
Friday.
</P>
<P>
Jacobs, 36, registered a time of 14:45.35 to win her second
title in the trials following her triumph in the 1,500 meters.
</P>
<P>
The time was about seven second better than her previous
American mark of 14:52.49. But she said she won't attempt an
Olympic double, preferring to stick to the shorter distance.
</P>
<P>
In decathlon, Tom Pappas edged world championships bronze
medalist Chris Huffins to win in 8,467 points. Huffins collected
8,285 to finish second.
</P>
<P>
Huffins had been regarded America's top decathlete in the past
two years as Olympic champion Dan O'Brien battled injury.
</P>
<P>
The 23-year-old Pappas said: "I'm kind of overwhelmed right now.
I thought I had a chance going into the second day if things went
right for me, and the vault gave me my chance." 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
