<HEADLINE> Olympic Champion Adkins Retires </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, July 21 (Xinhua) -- Reigning Olympic champion
Derrick Adkins has retired from competition in 400 meters hurdles
on Friday following his failure to qualify the Sydney Olympic
Games.
</P>
<P>
The 1996 Atlanta Olympic 400-meter hurdles gold medallist
failed to qualify for the final at the U.S. athletics Olympic
trials in Sacramento, California.
</P>
<P>
"This is my last race," said Adkins, who has been fighting
depression in the past four years.
</P>
<P>
"I'm in theology school, and right now I'm ready to get on with
the rest of my life," said the 30-year-old Adkins, who won the
Olympic gold in his hometown of Atlanta. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
