<HEADLINE> Foreign Trade Index of Major Chinese Regions: Shanghai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 22 (Xinhua) -- Xinhua is releasing dispatches on
major economic indicators of ten major Chinese regions in the
first half of this year. The ten regions include Guangdong,
Jiangsu, Shandong, Zhejiang, Henan, Liaoning, Shanghai, Beijing,
Tianjin and Chongqing. These provinces and municipalities make up
the bulk of the Chinese economy.
</P>
<P>
The following is the foreign trade index in Shanghai, China's
leading industrial and commercial center, in the first half of
this year:
</P>
<P>
Exports reached 11.76 billion US dollars, up 44.7 percent on a
yearly basis and the highest growth rate in the history. In the
first half, 860 foreign investment contracts were signed, up 12.6
percent from the year-ago period, involving a total capital of 2.2
billion US dollars, an increase of 6.3 percent. 
</P>
