<HEADLINE> Xinhua World Economic News Summary at 0500 GMT, July 22 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES -- Paraguayan government requested the
Interamerican Development Bank (IDB) a 320 million U.S. dollar
credit, said Friday Finance Minister Federico Zayas.
</P>
<P>
The resources will be used to compensate budget deficits for
the 2000-2001 period, said the minister, according to reports from
Asuncion, the Paraguayan capital. (Paraguay-Credit)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
WASHINGTON -- The U.S. federal government posted a fiscal
surplus of 56.3 billion U.S. dollars in June, 5.1 percent larger
than that recorded in the same month last year, the Treasury
Department reported Friday.
</P>
<P>
Revenue for June totaled 214.9 billion dollars, while
expenditures came to 158.6 billion dollars. (US-Surplus)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
LONDON - The UK economy has picked up strongly in the second
quarter of the year, according to official figures released Friday.
</P>
<P>
Gross domestic product is up 0.9 percent in the three months to
the end of June compared to 0.5 percent growth in the previous
quarter, provisional Office for National Statistics estimates
showed. (UK-Economy)
</P>
