<HEADLINE> Myanmar Exposes 277 Drug-related Cases in June </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, July 22 (Xinhua) -- The Myanmar authorities exposed a
total of 277 narcotic-drug-related cases in June this year,
seizing 141.1 kilos of opium and 1.21 kilos of heroin in the month,
official newspaper The New Light of Myanmar reported Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The seizure, made by army units, police and the customs, also
include 96.75 kilos of marijuana and 10.34 million tablets of
stimulant drugs.
</P>
<P>
During the month, the authorities punished 397 people -- 326
men and 71 women -- for being involved in the cases, the report
said.
</P>
<P>
According to the latest statistics of the Myanmar Central
Committee for Drug Abuse Control, the country seized a total of 1,
044 kilos of narcotic drugs in the first five months of this year.
</P>
<P>
During the same period, the authorities exposed a total of 1,
586 drug-related cases, punishing 2,170 drug offenders.
</P>
<P>
Up to now, there remains 89,500 hectares of poppy cultivation
in the country.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Myanmar is implementing a 255-million-U.S.-dollar 15-
year drug elimination plan which covers 51 cultivating and
producing townships. 
</P>
</TEXT>
