<HEADLINE> U.S. Soldiers Killed Two Albanians in Kosovo, Evidence Shows </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BELGRADE, July 21 (Xinhua) -- Conclusive evidence shows that
the killing of two ethnic Albanians in Gnjilane, Kosovo, last July
was committed by U.S. soldiers rather than by Serbs, a military
court in Gnjilane was told Friday.
</P>
<P>
Thirty-five U.S. soldiers of the NATO-led peacekeeping force in
Kosovo on duty on the night of July 10,1999 have unanimously
testified that U.S. soldiers in an observation post shot and
killed the two Albanians, French international judge Patrice de
Charette told the court on Friday.
</P>
<P>
He said the three Serb suspects who were arrested that night
and had been in custody in a U.S. base prison near Gnjilane would
be released soon, according to Yugoslav state news agency Tanjug.
</P>
</TEXT>
