<HEADLINE> One Year Ban for Australian Smart after Drugs Test </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, July 21 (Xinhua) -- Britain's Speedway Control Board
banned Australian rider Frank Smart for 12 months on Friday after
he failed a drugs test.
</P>
<P>
Smart, who rides for Swindon in southern England, was not
banned worldwide and no fine was imposed after he tested positive
for traces of amphetamines.
</P>
<P>
Smart apologized for his behavior and said he fully accepted
the decision. But he now had to consider his future.
</P>
<P>
Exeter rider Roger Lobb, who also failed a test, denied taking
drugs and said he was taking legal advice after asking for a
second sample to be tested. "I will fight all the way to clear my
name," he said.
</P>
<P>
The two riders were the first to test positive for drugs in
Britain for nearly three years. 
</P>
