<HEADLINE> Matthaeus To Rejoin Metrostars </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, July 21 (Xinhua) -- German veteran Lothar Matthaeus
will rejoin the New York-New Jersey MetroStars for training next
week after talks of three hours that ended a rift with the team.
</P>
<P>
"I think we can go a good way from here for the next three
months," Matthaeus said on Friday, "I hope to start training with
the team next week."
</P>
<P>
Matthaeus who has not played since injuring his back on June 28,
had the talks with commissioner Don Garber, MetroStars general
manager Nick Sakiewicz and coach Octavio Zambrano amid media
reports that the 39-year-old German opted to end his contract due
to conflicts of interests.
</P>
<P>
Matthaeus left the team in mid-May for Germany for the European
Championship. In his absence, the club went from one of the worst
clubs in the league to one of the best.
</P>
<P>
"All that happened, the problems prior to Euro 2000 plus his
injury ... right now we're looking a completely different face for
us," Zambrano said. "It would not be healthy to look at the past."
</P>
</TEXT>
