<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 0030 GMT, July 22 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON -- Scientists have found the first direct evidence
for the subatomic particle called the tau neutrino, the third kind
of neutrino known to particle physicists.
</P>
<P>
The breakthrough, announced Friday, was achieved by an
international collaboration of scientists at the U.S. Department
of Energy's Fermi National Accelerator Laboratory near Chicago. (
US-Tau Neutrino)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
