HARARE -- Zimbabwean President Robert Mugabe Friday attacked
white commercial farmers and some churches, saying they want to
retain European control on Zimbabwe.
</P>
<P>
Mugabe told the party's first Central Committee meeting after
the June parliamentary election that the white farmers had
retained their infrastructure and personnel to safeguard white
economic interests after independence. (Zimbabwe-President)
</P>
