<HEADLINE> Life Suspension for Cuban Weightlifter for Doping </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAVANA, July 21 (Xinhua) -- A Cuban weightlifter was banned for
life after failing a drug test earlier this month, Cuba's National
Sports Institute (INDER) announced in a statement published in
local daily newspaper Granma here on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Ernesto Montoya Laurencio of the 105 kg plus category failed an
international dope test carried out July 6 at a local tournament
in the eastern province of Holguin. He was found to have traces
of a performance-enhancing drug identified as "mantandienona".
</P>
<P>
"The Cuban sporting movement has been, is, and will be
intransigent in the case of any evidence of doping, a harmful and
unacceptable practice," the statement said.
</P>
<P>
Cuba is currently defending high-jump world record holder
Javier Sotomayor and three other weight-lifters, all of whom
failed dope tests at the Pan American Games in Canada last year
and had been banned by international federations. 
