<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Havana Residents To Parade on National Rebellion Day </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAVANA, July 22 (Xinhua) -- Residents of this capital city will
parade on July 26, the Day of National Rebellion commemoration,
past the United States Interests Office in Cuba.
</P>
<P>
On this day of the year 1953 a group of young revolutionaries,
led by Fidel Castro, raided the Moncada barracks, located in the
eastern city of Santiago de Cuba, an event that marked the start
of the end for the Fulgencio Batista dictatorship.
</P>
<P>
The Cuban Communist Party (PCC) called Saturday on the Havana
residents to hold the biggest parade of history, not only on
occasion of the historical date, but also as a demand to cease the
trade embargo imposed to Cuba by the United States near 40 years
ago.
</P>
<P>
Esteban Lazo, the top political leader in the capital city,
said that the parade will be characterized by a monolithic unity,
the revolutionary combativity, and the discipline, to show to the
world "the loyalty of a whole people to its party and to Fidel."
</P>
</TEXT>
